        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p>ISSUE TYPE: Story</p>

<p>Summary: Create vulnerable labs for cybersecurity application testing</p>

<p>Description:</p>

<p>Objective<br/>
Controlled vulnerable labs must be created to test the usability and effectiveness of our network cybersecurity application.</p>

<p>Context<br/>
To properly validate the application's detection, analysis, and response capabilities, simulated environments with real vulnerabilities are required, always within a secure and isolated setup.</p>

<p>Scope of Work</p>

<p>Carlos is responsible for:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Designing virtualized or isolated sandbox environments.</li>
	<li>Configuring intentionally vulnerable machines.</li>
	<li>Creating ransomware simulation scenarios (not real production malware).</li>
	<li>Configuring services with intentionally open ports for testing.</li>
	<li>Documenting the lab architecture.</li>
	<li>Ensuring full isolation from production networks.</li>
	<li>Creating usage guides for the testing team.</li>
	<li>Defining controlled attack scenarios for validation.</li>
</ul>


<p>Important<br/>
All labs must be fully isolated from real or production networks.</p>

<p>Acceptance Criteria</p>

<ul>
	<li>At least 4 functional vulnerable lab environments are created.</li>
	<li>Labs include ransomware simulation scenarios.</li>
	<li>Services with intentionally open ports are properly configured.</li>
	<li>Environments are fully isolated from production networks.</li>
	<li>The cybersecurity application can be tested successfully in the labs.</li>
	<li>Clear technical documentation is provided.</li>
</ul>


<p>Definition of Done (DoD)</p>

<ul>
	<li>Labs are functional and accessible to the team.</li>
	<li>Technical validation completed.</li>
	<li>Documentation approved.</li>
	<li>Network isolation verified.</li>
</ul>

            <br/>
        </td>
